cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with enhancing the spatial resolution of depth images, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method uses a guided filter and regularization to improve the upscaling results. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics-related techniques, such as cost aggregation and gradient regularization, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The regularization method is a form of optimization, which could be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
